    <p>The Sony Xpe­ria 1 II does not have a por­trait mode and did not do well in this cat­e­gory.</p>
    <p>The rest pro­duced a bokeh ef­fect, or back­ground blur­ring, while keep­ing their sub­jects sharp and clear.</p>
    <p>Thus, the real test is on a phone’s abil­ity to cap­ture white and skin colour ac­cu­rately.</p>
    <p>The Huawei P40 Pro was the best at this: cap­tur­ing the sub­ject’s skin tone ac­cu­rately while main­tain­ing the white bal­ance of the sur­round­ings.</p>
    <p>All the other cam­eras tend to un­der­ex­pose or over­ex­pose the sub­ject.</p>


